29 (c) Section 2-103.11(L) is modified to read as follows:
RMH H00703'25 (H-1) 05kzfo

3
1 "Employees are properly trained in food safety as it relates
2 to their assigned duties;Pf and".
3 (d) Section 6-501.115(B) is modified by the addition of
4 subparagraph (6) that reads as follows:
5 "(6) A dog that is controlled by a customer in a qualified
6 premises if all of the following apply:
7 (a) The qualified premises sells and serves only drinks.
8 (b) A health or safety hazard will not result from the
9 presence or activities of the dog.
10 (c) All of the following requirements are met:
11 (i) The qualified premises is maintained free of visible dog
12 hair, dog dander, and other dog-related waste and debris. The
13 qualified premises is cleaned and disinfected appropriately as
14 needed.
15 (ii) Surfaces contaminated by the waste created from a dog's
16 bodily functions are immediately cleaned and disinfected.
17 (iii) Equipment used to clean and that comes in contact with
18 waste from a dog's bodily functions is stored separate from all
19 other cleaning equipment and is not used for other cleaning
20 purposes.
21 (iv) All dog waste is disposed of at least daily outside of the
22 qualified premises in a covered waste receptacle.
23 (v) An employee who touches the dog or cleans waste from the
24 dog's bodily functions does not serve drinks or handle tableware
25 until the employee has washed the employee's hands.
26 (vi) The dog is not allowed on a seat, chair, or customer's
27 lap, or allowed to contact a tabletop, countertop, or similar
28 surface in the qualified premises.
29 (vii) The dog is not allowed to contact reusable tableware
RMH H00703'25 (H-1) 05kzfo

4
1 unless the tableware is dedicated for use by dogs and readily
2 distinguishable as such or is provided by the customer handling the
3 dog.
4 (viii) The dog is not allowed in an area where drinks are
5 prepared.
6 (ix) The dog is not unattended.
7 (x) The customer is 18 years of age or older.
8 (xi) The customer keeps the dog on a leash.
9 (d) The qualified premises may do any of the following:
10 (i) Determine the location and the amount of space designated
11 for a customer accompanied by a dog.
12 (ii) Establish a limit on the size and type of dog and any
13 other limitation relating to a customer's dog.
14 (iii) Deny entry or eject from the qualified premises a customer
15 and the customer's dog.".
16 (2) The director, by rule, may adopt any changes or updates to
17 the food code.
18 (3) The annexes of the food code are considered persuasive
19 authority for interpretation of the food code.
20 Enacting section 1. This amendatory act does not take effect
21 unless House Bill No. 4205 (request no. H00704'25) of the 103rd
22 Legislature is enacted into law.
